            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="nar.03259.001.jpg" type="verso"/>
           
            <ab>Aug. 9, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Hon. Geo. S. Boutwell,</ab>
            <ab>Secretary of the Treasury.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>I enclose a communication from Messrs. Sherwood &amp; Howland, Attorneys at Law, on the subject of the proceedings in the Eastern District of New York against the steamer "Cleopatra".</ab>
            <ab>As the matter is more appropriate to your Department than to this, I refer the papers to you.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully, &amp;c.</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman,</ab>
            <ab>Attorney General.</ab>
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">steamer "Cleopatra"</note>
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">New York</note>
            
            
            
